└─ Integration: Horizontal integration, rapid turnaround

Backup: Various providers (Rocket Lab, Astra, Relativity)
├─ For smaller batches and replenishment
├─ Higher cost but provides redundancy
└─ Important for geopolitical risk mitigation

Deployment Schedule:
Phase 1 (2027-2028): 1 pathfinder satellite (QS-1)
Phase 2 (2030-2032): 3-6 satellite test network
Phase 3 (2033-2035): 12-satellite pilot constellation
Phase 4 (2036-2040): Full 600-satellite deployment
Phase 5 (2041+): Continuous replenishment and upgrade

Orbital Operations:
├─ Station Keeping: ±1km box using electric propulsion
├─ Collision Avoidance: Automated using Space-Track data
├─ End-of-Life: Controlled deorbit within 5 years of retirement
├─ Space Debris: 95% burn-up on reentry design
└─ Compliance: Meets all UN and ITU space debris guidelines
```

