8. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP

8.1 Phase 0: Foundation (2024-2026)

```
Objectives:
1. Develop space-qualified quantum components
2. Establish manufacturing capabilities
3. Create international consortium
4. Develop protocols and standards

Key Milestones:
├─ Q2 2024: Consortium formation with 10+ nations
├─ Q4 2024: First integrated quantum photonic chip (TRL 4)
├─ Q2 2025: Space-qualified entangled photon source (TRL 5)
├─ Q4 2025: Ground station prototype operational
├─ Q2 2026: Complete system design review
└─ Q4 2026: Pathfinder satellite critical design review

Budget: $4 billion
Funding Sources: Governments (70%), Private investment (30%)
```

8.2 Phase 1: Pathfinder (2027-2029)

```
Objectives:
1. Demonstrate satellite-to-ground quantum links
2. Validate daytime operation
3. Test basic network protocols
4. Establish operational procedures

Key Missions:
├─ 2027: Airborne quantum link demonstration (aircraft to ground)
